com.camerontec.catalys.util.collection

Class NonDestructiveSetUtils

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.util.collection.NonDestructiveSetUtils

  • public final class NonDestructiveSetUtils
extends Object
    Utilities for common set operations.

    All operations supported by this class are guaranteed not to modify any of their operands.

      • difference

        public static <T> Set<T> difference(Set<T> s1,
                                    Set<T> s2)
        Calculate and return the asymmetric difference of two sets without modifying either operand.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The element type.
        Parameters:
        s1 - The first set.
        s2 - The second set.
        Returns:
        A set containing the elements contained in s1 that are not contained in s2. This is guaranteed not to be null, however, the caller must not assume that the iteration order is the same as for either operand.
